      objectReference: {fileID: 2276163250400312376}
    - target: {fileID: 5122842465899161861, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "Sweet Lavender\n\nIn cottage-maid's parterre thou'rt seen, \nIn simple
        touching grace ; \nAnd in the garden of the queen, \n'Midst costly plants
        and blossoms sheen, \nThou also hast a place. \nThe rose, with bright and
        peerless bloom, \nAttracted many eyes; \nBut while her glories and perfume
        \nExpire before brief summer's doom, \nThy fragrance never dies. \nBut thou
        art emblem of the friend, \nWho, whatsoe'er our lot, \nThe balm of faithful
        love will lend, \nAnd, true and constant to the end, \nMay die, but alters
        not.\n\n\u2014 Agnes Strickland"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5122842465899161861, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_TextStyleHashCode
      value: -1183493901
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5431834928911583797, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Sprite
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 1e03ef9b1e10bd541ab238eacd1c6fd8, type: 3}
    - target: {fileID: 5488519469664222319, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: "Lavender - Alfred Noyes (excerpt)\nLavender, lavender, \nFrom where
        the bee hums, \nTo the loud roar of London,\nWith purple dreams he comes,
        \nFrom ragged lanes of wild-Flowers\nTo ragged London slums, \nWith a basket
        full of lavender \nAnd purple dreams he comes."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5488519469664222319, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_TextStyleHashCode
      value: -1183493901
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5902464882853280731, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: instanceId
      value: cc3fc4e7-bc80-4c33-88d8-de3413f588b1
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5956918439778082410, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: the Name stems fron Latin "lavare" - washing. Romains laid it in Baths,
        beds and linen.
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5956918439778082410, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_TextStyleHashCode
      value: -1183493901
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5956918439778082416, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: already in acient times it was know that lavender wine helpts to ease
        "pains of the side and the nerves, and extreme cold." (De Matedia medica
        - Dioscorides)
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5956918439778082416, guid: ed7b740a5cf36044ab197a19d1fe05ab, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_TextStyleHashCode
      value: -1183493901
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
